            {
              "description": "Recognise the pattern in the sum",
              "working": "\\begin{align*}\\log_2(3) + \\log_4(3) + \\log_8(3) + \\ldots + \\log_{2^{10}}(3)\\end{align*}",
              "explanation": "Bases are 2¹, 2², 2³, ..., 2¹⁰"
            },
            {
              "description": "Apply change of base to each term",
              "working": "\\begin{align*}\\log_{2^k}(3) &= \\frac{\\log_2(3)}{\\log_2(2^k)} = \\frac{\\log_2(3)}{k}\\end{align*}",
              "explanation": "For k = 1, 2, 3, ..., 10"
            },
            {
              "description": "Write out the sum and factor",
              "working": "\\begin{align*}\\sum_{k=1}^{10} \\frac{\\log_2(3)}{k} &= \\log_2(3) \\left(\\frac{1}{1} + \\frac{1}{2} + \\frac{1}{3} + \\ldots + \\frac{1}{10}\\right)\\end{align*}",
              "explanation": "Factor out log_2(3) which is common to all terms"
            }
          ],
          "finalAnswer": "log₂(3) × (1 + 1/2 + 1/3 + ... + 1/10) or log₂(3) × H₁₀ where H₁₀ is the 10th harmonic number"
        }
